Two men have been sentenced to twenty years in prison by the Blue Downs Magistrates Court for killing a cop in Cape Town. Mxolisi Rhulumente (40) and Annesly David Campher (32) were each sentenced to 20 years imprisonment for the murder Sergeant Xoliza Mlindwa (41) who worked with the Gugulethu Crime Prevention unit. According to Lieutenant Colonel Philani Nkwalase, the body of the deceased cop was found by security officials with multiple gunshot wounds on the 30 June 2014 inside his vehicle. ALSO READ: COUNCILLOR RELEASED ON R3000 BAIL! “The security officials immediately alerted the local police who at the time managed to locate and secure some of his belongs at the crime scene. His official firearm was however missing,” Nkwalase said. Colonel Nkwalase said the Serious Organised Crime Investigation led to the recovery of the deceased firearm with ammunition. “Three suspects were arrested and charged for murder, armed robbery and possession of firearm and ammunition. "Rhulumente and Campher were both found guilty on all three charges in the Blue Downs Magistrates Court on 26 May 2020.  All charges were withdrawn against the third suspect,” Nkwalase added.